The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | More Holiday Inns to come up
                                                                                                               More Holiday Inns to come up
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, March 31: InterContinental Hotels Group (IHG) plans to open 20 hotels in India with over 5,000 rooms under its different brands  Holiday Inn, The InterContinental and Crowne Plaza .        
	The UK-based hotel chain, one of the worlds largest hospitality groups, is developing 14 Holiday Inn hotels in India with more than 3,700 rooms, which are scheduled to open over the next three years in 11 cities.        
	India is an important market for IHG, where both domestic and international traffic is increasing and new travel segments are opening up. In the Indian hotel business, the greatest opportunity for growth is in the mid-scale segment, in which Holiday Inn has a leading position, said Peter Gowers, chief executive (Asia Pacific), IHG.        
	IHG now has 13 hotels in India, including five Holiday Inn hotels. Gowers said Holiday Inn accounted for almost three quarters of the companys new developments in India.        
	Three of the 14 Holiday Inn hotels will be located in Calcutta and Bangalore. The others will come up in Delhi, Dehradun, Cochin, Coimbatore, Mumbai, Pune and Nagpur.        
	All 14 hotels will be new builds and will feature contemporary designs, including signature bedding and customised fragrance and music, the company said.        
	Holiday Inn has 1,381 hotels globally and 94 hotels across Asia Pacific.                                                                                                                                        
